parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall intermittently, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents. In some cases, it can also cause a fire, posing a risk to the occupants and bystanders.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls intermittently
the ignition switch fails to function properly
the vehicle catches fire due to an electrical short.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TFI module can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents. In some cases, it can also cause the vehicle to overheat.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
the vehicle becomes very hot
the TFI module fails to function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical wiring harness can cause a short circuit, leading to a fire, which can pose a risk to the occupants and bystanders.
symptoms: The wiring under the hood catches fire
an electrical short occurs in the wiring harness.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ECM can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
the ECM fails to function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt can cause serious injury or fatality in the event of an accident, as it may not provide adequate restraint to the occupant.
symptoms: The seat belt severs or breaks
the seat belt hangs loose
the seat belt snaps or fails to restrain the occupant during an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inadequate seat belt restraint can cause occupant ejection or failure to provide adequate protection during an accident, leading to serious injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt does not provide adequate restraint
the seat belt hangs loose
the occupant is not properly secured during an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical arcing from the catalytic converter can cause a fire hazard, potentially leading to a vehicle fire, which can result in damage to the vehicle and surrounding property, and may also cause injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Sparks or arcing observed from underneath the floorboard on the driver's side
near the catalytic converter.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent engine stalling can cause a loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when turning or driving at moderate speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle cuts off without prior warning
especially when driving at 40 mph and making turns
leaving the driver with little control over the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries. In severe cases, it can lead to fatal consequences.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
often without warning
even when the driver's foot is on the brake pedal. This can cause the vehicle to surge forward or backward
making it difficult to control.
